# Hot Cache

> Notes injected into context on every session boot. These are your most-accessed, highest-priority notes.
> Loaded automatically by `session-scan.sh` during SessionStart.

## How to populate

1. **Tier 1 (always loaded):** Notes you reference in >50% of sessions. Max 5 notes.
2. **Tier 2 (loaded if recent activity):** Notes active this week. Max 10 notes.
3. **Keep it small.** Every note here costs boot tokens. If you haven't referenced a note in 7+ days, move it out of hot-cache.
4. **Format:** `[[wikilink]]` with a brief reason for inclusion.
5. **Review weekly:** during your weekly review, prune stale entries and promote active ones.

